Habitat. Most specimens were collected with vessel-deployed box dredges in 20–42 m depth on muddy or sandy bottoms, sometimes with calcareous rubble. However, some specimens were collected in less than 0.7 m ( 2 feet ) of water (
Chace 1972
), while our material from southeastern Florida includes two juveniles collected with a yabby pump on a muddy-sandy intertidal grass flat.
